description: Recently we've woken not to the cheerful clatter of a kitchen nor boys bouncing balls in the garden, but to a toddler crying uncontrollably in a nearby house, writes Alexandra Shulman.
title: ALEXANDRA SHULMAN'S NOTEBOOK: Should I step in when the child in a nearby house won't stop crying?
